HEADWORD: Transfund
<hw>Trans*fund"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>transfundere</ets>; <ets>trans</ets> over, across +
<ets>fundere</ets> to pour, pour out. See <er>Found</er> to cast, and
cf. <er>Transfuse</er>.]</ety> <def>To pour from one vessel into
another; to transfuse.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Barrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

